I've already finished milking this one.
Let's look for another cow.\n< Serena>
Like this, like this, like this.\n< Serena>
Like this, like this, like this\n< Serena>

Hmm... I've only ever seen milk in a
container, so I had only recognized it
as such from the beginning...\n< Serena>

Somehow, I feel strange. I may no longer
be able to drink milk with the same
indifference as before.\n< Serena>

Is that so? For us, it's the opposite;
we don't feel anything anymore.\n< Farmer>

Well, originally it's something a mother
cow gives to her calf to drink.\n< Farmer>

The fact that we humans milk them and
drink it ourselves is, when you think
about it, quite a strange tale.\n< Farmer>

Wonder who was the first to think of
drinking it...\n< Farmer>
A mother, to her child...\n< Serena>
Hm? So does this cow have a child?\n< Serena>

That's right. Dairy cows are almost
always pregnant, you know.\n< Farmer>

Pregnant...?? What does that have to do
with milk?\n< Serena>

Ha, what a peculiar young lady. You must
have been really sheltered.\n< Farmer>

You see, a mother cow produces milk from
her udders to feed her calf.\n< Farmer>

In other words, they start producing
milk only after having a calf.\n< Farmer>

Using this creature's habits, us clever
humans have the cows stay pregnant all
year round so they keep producing milk.\n< Farmer>
Huh... Hmm...\n< Serena>

Is it that strange to you? After all,
not just cows but all mammals do that.\n< Farmer>

Even you were sucking on your mother's
milk until just the other day, weren't
you?\n< Farmer>
Humans too!?\n< Serena>

Of course. There isn't a human who grew
up without sucking on their mother's
milk.\n< Farmer>
I have never done such a thing...\n< Serena>

...No, now that I think about it
vaguely... I have memories of clinging
to my wet nurse's breast...\n< Serena>

...So when a child is born, will the
lord also produce milk?\n< Serena>
Me? Ah-hahaha!!\n< Farmer>
Hm...?\n< Serena>

Nah, I won't. Producing milk is the
mother's job.\n< Farmer>

If anything, it would be your job, not
mine. The job of producing milk, that
is.\n< Farmer>
Me!?\n< Serena>
Like this...?\n< Serena>

Humans and cows have different breast
sizes. It shouldn't be with such force.\n< Farmer>
Is that so...\n< Serena>

Well, think of it as practice for
someday. Go on and give it a try.\n< Farmer>

When you say it like that, it makes it
even harder to do...\n< Serena>
\n< Serena>...

\n< Farmer>No need for any more instructions, huh?
You've gotten quite used to this.
セレナ HK_FM01-1
セレナ HK_FM01-1

Even if I'm used to it, I'm only working
at half the speed of you, Master.\n< Serena>

Well, that's because I make my living
off of this.\n< Farmer>

Alright, I'm done here. Can I leave the
last two to you?\n< Farmer>

\n< Serena>Hmm, it seems it won't come out anymore.
You behaved very well, good job.

\n< Serena>My lord, it's finished, but... why are
you lying on the ground?

\n< Farmer>No, I thought maybe I could see if I did
this...
\n< Serena>See what?
\n< Farmer>What indeed...

\n< Serena>??... Anyway, the job is done. Does this
mean the request is complete?
\n< Farmer>Eh? Oh... Ah! Yes, that's right!

\n< Farmer>Of course, of course. This is the last
of it. Phew- you've been a great help.

\n< Farmer>I'll make sure to speak well of you to
the guild too.

\n< Farmer>...If possible, I'd like another
excellent adventurer like you to come
help again.

\n< Serena>That is... I apologize, but I am also in
a hurry, so I cannot make any promises.

\n< Serena>However, if circumstances allow, I shall
visit again.

\n< Serena>There's a difference between horses and
cows, but it was fun to interact with
animals after such a long time...

\n< Farmer>Heh heh. Is that so, is that so. Well
then, I'll be counting on you again.
\n< Serena>Ah. Until then.
\n< Guild Master>Oh, you're back. How did it go?

\n< Serena>It finished without any problems. Please
record the completion of the request.

\n< Guild Master>Nah, I'm not talking about that... If
there were no problems, then that's more
than we could ask for...

\n< Guild Master>Well, never mind. Here's your reward for
this request.
\n< Serena>Hmm... \V[2501] left...

It's a rope.\n< Serena>

I suppose there are countless uses for
it on a farm like this.\n< Serena>
It's the feed box.\n< Serena>

You scoop from here to feed the
livestock.\n< Serena>

I've tried it once, but it was such hard
labor that I quickly had a servant take
over.\n< Serena>
It's a whip.\n< Serena>

They say it's used to strike the ground
and intimidate the livestock when they
absolutely won't listen.\n< Serena>

Judging by the dust on it, it seems it's
hardly used around here.\n< Serena>
\n< Serena>So, what's with this outfit?

\n< Farmer>You can't work in the stables wearing
such a pretty dress, can you?
\n< Serena>Well, that's true but...

\n< Farmer>It's good that the child size fits you
well.

\n< Farmer>So... you're used to handling livestock,
but you've never milked before, right?

\n< Serena>Yes. But I'm confident in my ability to
learn. Just show me a little and I think
I can do it right away.

\n< Farmer>Heh, is that so? Well, I'm going to milk
now, so watch closely and learn.
